and why this is so dangerous.

00:17:51.700 --> 00:17:55.120 align:middle line:84%
In his book "Origin of
Species," what Darwin said,

00:17:55.120 --> 00:17:58.180 align:middle line:84%
he believed that
life was a struggle.

00:17:58.180 --> 00:18:00.460 align:middle line:10%
And while he believed
that on the one hand,

00:18:00.460 --> 00:18:04.270 align:middle line:10%
he also prefaces his
own words by telling us

00:18:04.270 --> 00:18:07.760 align:middle line:10%
what he's about to say to us
doesn't make a lot of sense.

00:18:07.760 --> 00:18:09.760 align:middle line:84%
So I want you to see
what he's saying,

00:18:09.760 --> 00:18:11.050 align:middle line:90%
and just hear his own words.

00:18:11.050 --> 00:18:16.670 align:middle line:84%
Darwin said, quote, it may
not be a logical deduction,

00:18:16.670 --> 00:18:21.170 align:middle line:84%
but it is far more satisfactory
to look at instincts,

00:18:21.170 --> 00:18:25.280 align:middle line:84%
such as ants making
slaves of other ants

00:18:25.280 --> 00:18:30.010 align:middle line:84%
as small examples of
one general law leading

00:18:30.010 --> 00:18:32.620 align:middle line:84%
to the advancement
of all beings.

00:18:32.620 --> 00:18:36.490 align:middle line:84%
And that law is the law that
says we should multiply.

00:18:36.490 --> 00:18:40.020 align:middle line:10%
We should vary, let
the strongest live,

00:18:40.020 --> 00:18:42.060 align:middle line:10%
and the weakest die.

00:18:42.060 --> 00:18:46.260 align:middle line:10%
Let the strongest live
and the weakest die.

00:18:46.260 --> 00:18:49.200 align:middle line:84%
This is such a
dangerous way to think.

00:18:49.200 --> 00:18:51.650 align:middle line:84%
And it's dangerous for
a couple of reasons,

00:18:51.650 --> 00:18:53.970 align:middle line:84%
particularly because of
when it was introduced,

00:18:53.970 --> 00:18:56.370 align:middle line:90%
late 1800s, early 1900s.

